Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, bellmansgapc (>= 2024.01.11), libgsl0-dev, libgmp3-dev, libgsl0-dev (>= 1.13), libgsl0ldbl (>= 1.13), libfoldgrammars (>= 1.2.99), ghc (>=7.4.1) | ghc6 (>=6.12.1), libmath-round-perl ( >= 0.06-3)
Description:  Covariance models (CMs), as defined by Sean Eddy, do not reward insertions of valid base-pairs or complete sub-structures relative to the one consensus secondary structure. Nevertheless, some families, e. g. tRNA, contain minorities with additional informative sub-structures, which are crashed by the majority during formation of one consensus secondary structure. Ambivalent Covariance Models (aCMs) are our prototypic suggestion to extend CMs with more than one consensus structure.